library(statip)

Simualte a 2-state Markov chain

n <- 500
y <- seq(0,0,length.out=n)
s1 <- seq(0,0,length.out=n+1)
s2 <- seq(0,0,length.out=n+1)
e <- rnorm(n, mean = 0, sd = 1)
s1[1] <- 0 # initialize 
s2[1] <- 1
for (i in 1:500) {
  if (s1[i]==1)  {
    y[i] <- 1 + e[i]            # model in state 1
    
    s1[i+1] <- rbern(1, 0.7)
    if (s1[i+1]==0) {
      s2[i+1] <- 1
    } else {
      s2[i+1] <- 0
    }
    
    
  } else {
    y[i] <- -1 + e[i]
    
    s2[i+1] <- rbern(1, 0.9)
    if (s2[i+1]==0) {
      s1[i+1] <- 1
    } else {
      s1[i+1] <- 0
    }
  }
  
}
plot(y, type="l")
